 039        var isAuthenticated = false;
 040        var reqUsername = String.Empty;
 041        var reqPassword = String.Empty;
 42        try
 43        {
 044            var authHeader = AuthenticationHeaderValue.Parse(Request.Headers["Authorization"]);
 045            var credentialBytes = Convert.FromBase64String(authHeader.Parameter);

 047            reqUsername = credentials[0];
 048            reqPassword = credentials[1];
 49
 050            var apiUsername = _configuration.GetSection("ApiCredentials")["Username"];
 051            var apiPassword = _configuration.GetSection("ApiCredentials")["Password"];
 52
 053            isAuthenticated = reqUsername == apiUsername && reqPassword == apiPassword;
 054        }
 55        catch
 56        {
 057            await Task.CompletedTask;
 58
 059            return AuthenticateResult.Fail("Invalid Authorization Header");
 60        }
 61
 062        if (!isAuthenticated)
 63        {
 064            return AuthenticateResult.Fail("Invalid Username or Password");
 65        }
 66
 067        var claims = new[] {
 068                new Claim(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier, reqUsername),
 069                new Claim(ClaimTypes.Name, reqUsername),
 070            };
 071        var identity = new ClaimsIdentity(claims, Scheme.Name);
 072        var principal = new ClaimsPrincipal(identity);
 073        var ticket = new AuthenticationTicket(principal, Scheme.Name);
 74
 075        return AuthenticateResult.Success(ticket);
 076    }

 2287                        message.MarAsProcessed();
 288
 2289                        await processingDbContext.SaveChangesAsync(cancellationToken);
 290
 2291                        await transaction.CommitAsync(cancellationToken);
 292
 2293                        EventsMeters.DomainOutbox_MessagesProcessed.Add(1);
 2294                        EventsMeters.DomainOutbox_DispatchDurationMs.Record(messageStopwatch.Elapsed.TotalMilliseconds);
 2295                    }
 0296                    catch (Exception ex)
 297                    {
 0298                        _logger.LogError(ex, "Outbox dispatch failed for {Id}", message.Id);
 299
 300                        // rollback transacation and backoff
 301                        try
 302                        {
 0303                            await transaction.RollbackAsync(cancellationToken);
 0304                        }
 0305                        catch (Exception transactionException)
 306                        {
 0307                            _logger.LogWarning(transactionException, "Failed to rollback transaction for message {Id}", 
 0308                        }
 309
 0310                        dispatcherActivity?.AddEvent(new ActivityEvent("handler.error", tags: new ActivityTagsCollection
 0311                            {
 0312                                { "exception.message", ex.Message },
 0313                                { "exception.details", ex.ToBetterString() },
 0314                            }));
 315
 0316                        message.Backoff();
 317
 0318                        await processingDbContext.SaveChangesAsync(cancellationToken);
 319
 0320                        EventsMeters.DomainOutbox_MessagesFailed.Add(1);
 0321                        EventsMeters.DomainOutbox_DispatchDurationMs.Record(messageStopwatch.Elapsed.TotalMilliseconds);
 0322                    }
 323                    finally
 324                    {
 2325                        messageStopwatch.Stop();
 326                    }
 2327                }
 2328            }
 4329            catch (Exception ex)
 330            {
 4331                _logger.LogError(ex, $"{nameof(DomainEventDispatcher)} loop error");
 4332            }
 333
 4334            loopStopwatch.Stop();
 335
 4336            EventsMeters.DomainOutbox_LoopDurationMs.Record(loopStopwatch.Elapsed.TotalMilliseconds);
 4337        }
 338
 4339        _logger.LogInformation("OutboxDispatcher stopped");
 4340    }

 342    private static TimeSpan AddJitter(TimeSpan baseDelay, double jitterFactor = 0.2)
 343    {
 4344        var extraMs = baseDelay.TotalMilliseconds * jitterFactor * Random.Shared.NextDouble();
 345

 352    private static Task InvokeHandler(object handler, object envelope, CancellationToken cancellationToken)
 353    {
 2354        ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull(handler);
 2355        ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull(envelope);
 356
 2357        var handlerType = handler.GetType();
 2358        var key = (HandlerType: handlerType, EnvelopeType: envelope.GetType());
 2359        var invoker = _dispatchers.GetOrAdd(key, x =>
 2360        {
 2361            var methods = x.HandlerType.GetMethods(BindingFlags.Public | BindingFlags.Instance)
 2362                .Where(x => x.Name == nameof(IDomainEventHandler<object>.HandleAsync))
 2363                .ToArray();
 2364
 2365            var method = methods.FirstOrDefault(x => x.GetParameters().First().ParameterType == key.EnvelopeType);
 2366
 2367            if (method is null)
 2368            {
 0369                throw new InvalidOperationException($"Handler {handler.GetType().FullName} does not have a public Handle
 2370            }
 2371
 2372            return (handler, envelope, cancellationToken) => (Task)method.Invoke(handler, [envelope, cancellationToken])
 2373        });
 374
 2375        return invoker(handler, envelope, cancellationToken);
 376    }

 379    private static async Task<Guid[]> GetMessagesToProcessAsync(MessagingDbContext context, int maxAttempts, int batchSi
 380    {
 0381        using var _ = SuppressInstrumentationScope.Begin(); // no telemetry, avoid flooding it with idle loops data
 382
 0383        var now = DateTime.UtcNow; // close enough for "due" check
 384
 0385        var candidateIds = await context.Set<DomainOutboxMessage>()
 0386            .AsNoTracking()

 0388            .NotClaimed(now)
 0389            .OrderBy(x => x.CreatedUtc)

 0391            .Take(batchSize)

 395        {
 0396            return Array.Empty<Guid>();
 397        }
 398
 0399        var claimedCount = await context.Set<DomainOutboxMessage>()

 0401            .Due(now, maxAttempts)
 0402            .NotClaimed(now)

 0404                .SetProperty(x => x.ClaimedBy, x => iterationId)
 0405                .SetProperty(x => x.ClaimedUntil, x => now.Add(claimTimeToLive)), cancellationToken);
 406
 0407        if (claimedCount == 0)
 408        {
 0409            return Array.Empty<Guid>();
 410        }
 411
 0412        var claimedIds = await context.Set<DomainOutboxMessage>()
 0413            .AsNoTracking()
 0414            .ClaimedBy(iterationId, now)
 0415            .OrderBy(x => x.CreatedUtc)
 0416            .Select(x => x.Id)
 0417            .ToArrayAsync(cancellationToken);
 418
 0419        return claimedIds;
 0420    }

 33    internal void Backoff()
 34    {
 035        Attempts++;
 036        DoNotProcessBeforeUtc = DateTime.UtcNow.Add(ComputeBackoff(Attempts));
 037        ClaimedUntil = null;
 038        ClaimedBy = null;
 039    }

 41    internal void MarAsProcessed()
 42    {
 243        ProcessedUtc = DateTime.UtcNow;
 244        ClaimedUntil = null;
 245        ClaimedBy = null;
 246        Attempts++;
 247    }

 49    internal void MarkAsPoisoned()
 50    {

 052        ClaimedUntil = null;
 053        ClaimedBy = null;
 054        Attempts++;

 57    private TimeSpan ComputeBackoff(int attempts)
 58    {
 59        // Exponential backoff with a maximum of 300 seconds (5 minutes)
 060        var baseSeconds = Math.Min(300, (int)Math.Pow(2, Math.Min(10, attempts)));
 61
 062        var jitter = Random.Shared.Next(0, 1000);
 63
 064        var backoff = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(baseSeconds).Add(TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(jitter));
 65
 066        return backoff;
 67    }

 300    private static TimeSpan AddJitter(TimeSpan baseDelay, double jitterFactor = 0.2)
 301    {

 320public static class IntegrationOutboxQueryExtensions
 321{
 322    public static IQueryable<IntegrationOutboxMessage> Due(this IQueryable<IntegrationOutboxMessage> query, DateTime now
 323    {
 4324        ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull(query);
 325
 4326        return query
 4327            .Where(x => x.ProcessedUtc == null)
 4328            .Where(x => !x.IsPoisoned)
 4329            .Where(x => x.DoNotProcessBeforeUtc == null || x.DoNotProcessBeforeUtc <= now)
 4330            .Where(x => x.ClaimedUntil == null || x.ClaimedUntil < now)
 4331            .Where(x => x.Attempts < maxAttempts);
 332    }
 333
 334    public static IQueryable<IntegrationOutboxMessage> ClaimedBy(this IQueryable<IntegrationOutboxMessage> query, Guid c
 335    {
 2336        ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull(query);
 337
 2338        return query
 2339            .Where(x => x.ClaimedBy == claimedBy)
 2340            .Where(x => x.ClaimedUntil != null && x.ClaimedUntil >= now);

 24
 25    // Time when the message was published to the broker, so it was
 26    // processed in the outbox, but each consumer will later process it
 27    // with their own logic

 033    public bool IsPoisoned { get; private set; }
 34
 35    internal void Backoff()
 36    {
 037        Attempts++;
 038        DoNotProcessBeforeUtc = DateTime.UtcNow.Add(ComputeBackoff(Attempts));
 039        ClaimedUntil = null;
 040        ClaimedBy = null;
 041    }
 42
 43    internal void MarkAsProcessed()
 44    {
 245        ProcessedUtc = DateTime.UtcNow;
 246        ClaimedUntil = null;
 247        ClaimedBy = null;
 248        Attempts++;
 249    }
 50
 51    internal void MarkAsPoisoned()
 52    {
 053        IsPoisoned = true;
 054        ClaimedUntil = null;
 055        ClaimedBy = null;
 056        Attempts++;
 057    }
 58
 59    private TimeSpan ComputeBackoff(int attempts)
 60    {
 61        // Exponential backoff with a maximum of 300 seconds (5 minutes)
 062        var baseSeconds = Math.Min(300, (int)Math.Pow(2, Math.Min(10, attempts)));
 63
 064        var jitter = Random.Shared.Next(0, 1000);
 65
 066        var backoff = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(baseSeconds).Add(TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(jitter));
 67
 068        return backoff;
 69    }

 144    private static string ConvertToString(object value, Type targetType)

 1using System.Security.Cryptography;

 3namespace rbkApiModules.Commons.Core;
 4
 5public static class PasswordHasher
 6{
 7    /// <summary>
 8    /// Método para gerar um hash a partir de uma senha
 9    /// </summary>
 10    /// <param name="password">Senha do usuário</param>
 11    public static string GenerateSaltedHash(string password)
 12    {
 513        var saltBytes = new byte[64];
 514        RandomNumberGenerator.Fill(saltBytes);
 515        string salt = Convert.ToBase64String(saltBytes);
 16
 517        var rfc2898DeriveBytes = new Rfc2898DeriveBytes(password, saltBytes, 100000, HashAlgorithmName.SHA512);
 518        string hash = Convert.ToBase64String(rfc2898DeriveBytes.GetBytes(256));
 19
 520        return salt + hash;
 21    }
 22
 23    /// <summary>
 24    /// Método para conferir se uma senha em hash confere com uma senha digitada
 25    /// </summary>
 26    /// <param name="enteredPassword">Senha digitada</param>
 27    /// <param name="hashedPassword">Senha salva no banco</param>
 28    /// <returns></returns>
 29    public static bool VerifyPassword(string enteredPassword, string hashedPassword)
 30    {
 531        var salt = hashedPassword.Substring(0, 88);
 532        var hash = hashedPassword.Substring(88, hashedPassword.Length - 88);
 33
 534        var saltBytes = Convert.FromBase64String(salt);
 535        var rfc2898DerivedBytes = new Rfc2898DeriveBytes(enteredPassword, saltBytes, 100000, HashAlgorithmName.SHA512);
 36
 537        return Convert.ToBase64String(rfc2898DerivedBytes.GetBytes(256)) == hash;

 48        // In this case, they match, so we could return empty dictionary

 72    private void ApplyDatabaseConstraints()
 73    {
 74        try
 75        {
 576            var entityType = Context.Model.FindEntityType(typeof(TModel));
 577            if (entityType == null)

 80            }

 583            var ignoredProperties = GetIgnoredProperties().ToHashSet();
 84
 585            foreach (var property in entityType.GetProperties())
 86            {
 587                var requestPropertyName = GetRequestPropertyName(property.Name, propertyMappings);
 88

 90                {
 91                    continue;

 595                if (requestProperty == null)

 5102        }
 0103        catch (Exception ex)

 106            // even if there are issues with the database configuration

 152    private void ApplyRequiredConstraint(PropertyInfo requestProperty)
 153    {
 5154        var propertyType = requestProperty.PropertyType;
 155
 5156        if (propertyType == typeof(string))
 157        {
 5158            CreateRuleFor<string>(requestProperty)
 5159                .NotEmpty()
 5160                .WithMessage(GetLocalizedMessage("Required", requestProperty.Name));
 161        }
 5162        else if (propertyType == typeof(Guid))
 163        {
 5164            CreateRuleFor<Guid>(requestProperty)
 5165                .NotEmpty()
 5166                .WithMessage(GetLocalizedMessage("Required", requestProperty.Name));
 167        }

 169        {
 170            // For non-nullable value types, we don't need to add required validation
 171            // as they can't be null anyway
 172        }
 173        else
 174        {
 1175            CreateRuleFor<object>(requestProperty)
